item.title: Brittany add a quote by Georgette Heyer
item.description: "You're only a man! You've not our gifts! I can tell you! Why, a woman can think of a hundred different things at once, all them contradictory!" -- Georgette Heyer

item.title: Brittany add a quote by Jane Austen
item.description: "The person, be it gentleman or lady, who has not pleasure in a good novel, must be intolerably stupid." -- Jane Austen

item.title: Brittany add a quote by Jennifer Crusie
item.description:
"He was not looking forward to breaking the law. He was straight now. He'd matured. Crime no longer excited him.
What?' Ronald said.
I didn't say anything.'
You're breathing heavy." -- Jennifer Crusie

item.title: Brittany add a quote by J.K. Rowling

item.title: Brittany add a quote by J.K. Rowling
